        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare genetic form of pontocerebellar hypoplasia (PCH) characterized by neocortical and pontocerebellar hypoplasia with pons and cerebellum equally affected and that clinically manifests with neonatal hypotonia and impaired swallowing followed by seizures optic atrophy and short stature from infancy onward. Movement disorders as seen in other forms of PCH are absent."
        },
